A Short Bitcoin ETF also known as Inverse Bitcoin ETF is a fund that allows investors the opportunity to hedge in on decrease in price of Bitcoin. In other words as the price of Bitcoin decreases they (the investors) profit from it.

These ETFs track the price of Bitcoin and any correlated assets without actually owning Bitcoin itself. Futures Bitcoin ETFs on the other hand are bitcoin contracts that are bought at a specific amount at a specific time and for a specific price! These also give investors and

Bitcoin but in ETFs and not real Bitcoins. There are a three types of ETFs and I'm gonna touch on all three - Spot Bitcoin ETF Futures Bitcoin ETF and Inverse Bitcoin ETF. Spot Bitcoin ETF are contracts that allow investors to buy Bitcoin ETFs at the current price.
